    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Depictions in which the entire body of the person is portrayed, as contrasted to a portrait of only the face, a bust, or a half-length portrayal. The sitter may be standing or sitting in his or her entirety, and is often portrayed life-size or larger.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000049830/Oxford Companion to Western Art [online] (2008-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Afbeeldingen waarbij het hele lichaam van de betreffende persoon is afgebeeld en bijvoorbeeld niet alleen diens gezicht en eventueel de buste of romp. Het model kan staan of zitten en wordt vaak levensgroot of nog groter afgebeeld.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099090/Van Dale Online Woordenboek (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052654/Mardoc</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000087761/MARDOC</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Darstellung, die den ganzen Körper einer Person abbildet, im Gegensatz zu einem Porträt nur des Gesichtes, einer Büste oder einem Halbfigurenporträt. Das Modell kann stehend oder sitzend in Gänze und oft lebensgroß oder größer dargestellt sein.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>人物的全身描繪圖，與只描繪臉部、胸部或半身的肖像畫不同。全身人像之畫中人物可能以站或坐姿呈現，尺寸則通常與實際相符或者更大。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
